osts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 4:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4412.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What Happened?</span><hr size=1> It has always interested me to play on this server, the thought of playing in a role-playing environment, the TLC to eliminate farming of the rare spawns, 1 character per account to rid us of the pure twinks, no common language (how in the world can a Troll speak to a Vah Shir without having learned their tongue), no /ooc to make a more fantasy environment, limited /shout range (is it really possible to hear someone clear across the zone of OOT), /auction only available inside the city walls where business should be done, and the idea of having to devote time into learning a language, rather than quick fix of spam. Alas, all of this gone except the TLC, my heart is now heavy, feeling as if this is just another blue server. My concern and question: Is the spirit still alive? Is this still a role-playing server, or have we been sold out? Thank you my friends. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnicholasfv>GnicholasFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 4:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4412.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Happened?</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry. We can't do anything without a receipt. <br>
<br>
Gnic <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=freelancewizard>FreelanceWizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 4:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4412.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Happened?</span><hr size=1> Yes. There are still more role-players here than anywhere else, IMHO. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.realitywerks.com/hosted-images/elludensig.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xsasx>Xsasx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 5:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4412.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Happened?</span><hr size=1> I notice that when I RP, I tend to get it back.  I try to make sure I make OOC comments as well to let them know to not take it personally.  If I do not get RP back to me, then I talk with them anyway.  I don't live and die to RP.<br>
<br>
Iksar are superior after all.  An Iksar Necromancer makes alot of fun to play, especially when you mix in some random kindesses.  Like just last night when some poor human was doing a CR and was waiting on the Nexus pad to NK.  They were doing some emotes about their stomach growling.  I gave them a couple of fish rolls and told them don't spread it around.  While one could argue not totally IC, others had some fun snickering at my arrogance in bragging about Iksars.<br>
<br>
