Xsasx</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/dot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 1617<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 5:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4412.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/smile.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Happened?</span><hr size=1> I ask the same question and have even considered quitting altogether because of the bleakness of the answer most days.  <br>
<br>
Yes, there are still a lot who RP, but the droves of those who not only do not but mock those who do is growing.  Yes, there are still a lot who think there is more to the game than the stats and numbers, but the hoardes who think those numbers are so important they need to pad them in any way possible (i.e. using RL money to do so) is growing. <br>
<br>
Each time I get overwhelmed with the OOC, I wonder if this game isn't just another form of DII and I couldn't stand playing that on Bnet because of the d00ds and griefers and bored of it in single player rather quickly.  <p><center><table width="55%"><tr><td align="center">
